ECHO OFF
* **Removed non-DotScript PowerShell tail** (`$py12=...` / `& ...`) and replaced with a **BANG**-style optional Python smoke call (commented).
* **SQLite**: replaced invalid `SQLITE DB ...` with **`SQLITE OPEN ...`** (matches your current SQLITE help).
* **Relations**: removed `REL_LIST`, `REL_REFRESH`, `CMDREL...` variants that tend to be “unknown command” noise (kept the canonical `REL ...` forms).
* **Cross-area tuple**: fixed bad reference `#11.LNAME` (TERMS has no LNAME). Replaced with `#10.LNAME` (TEACHERS).
* **CALCWRITE section**: removed assignment-form `CALC GPA = ...` (script-level grammar risk). Uses **`CALCWRITE`** so any failure is on the program feature, not the script.
* **Control blocks**: removed `UNTIL/ENDUNTIL` and `LOOP/ENDLOOP` (high risk of being unsupported keywords). Kept **IF/ELSE/ENDIF**, **WHILE/ENDWHILE**, **SCAN/ENDSCAN** only.
* Tightened a few canary comparisons with explicit parentheses for clarity.

* ============================================================
* MCC_EXHAUSTIVE_FULL_REGRESSION_CANARIES.DTS  (CLEANED)
*
* PURPOSE:
* - Thorough regression / canary sweep for DotTalk++ core CLI + DotScript.
* - Avoids script-caused failures/noise: only genuine program behavior should fail.
*
* RULES / ASSUMPTIONS:
* - CALC comparisons (= <> <= >= < >) are wrapped in parentheses.
* - Quotes required for values with spaces; otherwise optional. (We quote most strings anyway.)
* - ASCII ONLY. Inline comments use '*'.
* ";" is comment continuation, ";;" is intended for sqlite input at the command line,
* - the shell ignores it as continuation and then strips one semi-colon, leaving the remainder ";" for use in SQLITE scripts.
* ============================================================

ECHO ===== EXHAUSTIVE FULL REGRESSION START =====
COLOR DEFAULT
VERSION

ECHO ===== HELP / CATALOG SANITY =====
HELP
HELP /PRED
* PREDHELP
* PREDICATES
* FOXHELP
* FOXHELP SCHEMA
* FOXHELP REL
* CMDHELP
* CMDHELPCHK
* CMDARGCHK

ECHO ===== PATHS / ROOTS =====
SETPATH
SETPATH RESET
SETPATH
DIR
DIR data
DIR dbf
DIR indexes
DIR tmp

ECHO ===== STARTUP / DIAGNOSTICS =====
INIT
DBAREA
DBAREAS
AREA
STATUS
WS
* SHOW PART OF OTHER SYSTEM
AREA
SHOW FILTER
SHOW BREADCRUMBS
CALC DATE()

ECHO ===== SCHEMAS BRING-UP =====
SCHEMAS
SCHEMAS CLOSE
REL CLEAR ALL
SCHEMAS OPEN DBF
SCHEMAS

ECHO ===== BASELINE CLOCK / DATE-TIME =====
DATE
TODAY
TIME
NOW
DATETIME
CALC DATE()
CALC TODAY()
CALC TIME()
CALC NOW()
CALC DATETIME()
ECHO [CANARY DATE=TODAY] Expect .T.:
CALC (DATE() = TODAY())
ECHO [CANARY NOW=DATETIME] Expect .T.:
CALC (NOW() = DATETIME())

ECHO ===== CANARIES: DATE ALGEBRA + COMPARISONS =====
CALC (DATE() + 2)
CALC (DATE() - 2)
ECHO [CANARY DATE-CMP-1] Expect .T.:
CALC ((DATE() + 2) > DATE())
ECHO [CANARY DATE-CMP-2] Expect .T.:
CALC ((DATE() - 2) < DATE())

ECHO ===== CTOD / DTOC =====
ECHO [CANARY CTOD-UNQUOTED-HYPHEN] Expect clean error (hyphen date must be quoted):
CTOD 2000-01-01

CTOD "2000-01-01"
CTOD "2000/01/01"
CTOD 20000101

CALC CTOD("2000-01-01")
CALC DTOC(CTOD("2000-01-01"))
ECHO [CANARY DTOC-ROUNDTRIP] Expect .T.:
CALC (DTOC(CTOD("2000-01-01")) = "20000101")

ECHO [CANARY DATE+1 EQ] Expect .T.:
CALC ((CTOD("2000-01-01") + 1) = CTOD("2000-01-02"))
ECHO [CANARY DATE-1 EQ] Expect .T.:
CALC ((CTOD("2000-01-01") - 1) = CTOD("1999-12-31"))

ECHO ===== DATEADD / DATEDIFF (command + CALC) =====
ECHO [CANARY DATEADD cmd] Expect 20000131:
DATEADD 20000101 30
ECHO [CANARY DATEADD cmd neg] Expect 19991202:
DATEADD 20000101 -30
ECHO [CANARY DATEDIFF cmd] Expect 1:
DATEDIFF 20000102 20000101

CALC DATEADD(DATE(), 30)
CALC DATEDIFF(DATE(), CTOD("2000-01-01"))

ECHO ===== CANARIES: RHS EXPRESSIONS IN COMPARISONS =====
ECHO [CANARY RHS-EQ-1] Expect .T.:
CALC (3 = (1 + 2))
ECHO [CANARY RHS-EQ-2] Expect .T.:
CALC ((1 + 2) = (6 / 2))
ECHO [CANARY RHS-EQ-3] Expect .T.:
CALC ((1 + (2 * 3)) = (1 + (2 * 3)))

ECHO ===== STRING / CHAR COMMANDS =====
